<blockquote local-id=3D"3e6e13b7-eedd-497e-9c1f-f6ac534296a0">
<p local-id=3D"2f6fe5b70a76">=E2=9C=94 <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Alw=
ays deploy RAR (RFC 9396) and PAR (RFC 9126) together in financial applicat=
ions. RAR provides the semantic precision required by PSD2 and Open Banking=
 standards. PAR ensures that this semantically rich =E2=80=94 and therefore=
 highly sensitive =E2=80=94 payload never appears in a browser URL, a proxy=
 log, or a SIEM event. Either extension in isolation leaves a significant g=
ap: RAR without PAR exposes detailed financial data in URLs; PAR without RA=
R secures the transport of a payload that is still semantically insufficien=
t for regulatory compliance.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"b2dbdb9d-bdd6-4db1-a981-11a526574de6">
<h2 local-id=3D"5bf41cd30b39" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-Part3=E2=80=94Fine-G=
rainedAuthorizationwithaPolicyDecisionPoint(PDP)">Part 3 =E2=80=94 Fine-Gra=
ined Authorization with a Policy Decision Point (PDP)</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"a44d6c6bb386" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-Part3=E2=80=94Fine-G=
rainedAuthorizationwithaPolicyDecisionPoint(PDP).1">Part 3 =E2=80=94 Fine-G=
rained Authorization with a Policy Decision Point (PDP)</h3>
<h3 local-id=3D"069852babc40" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-3.1TheRemainingGap=
=E2=80=94TokenIssuanceisNotAuthorizationEnforcement">3.1 The Remaining Gap =
=E2=80=94 Token Issuance is Not Authorization Enforcement</h3>
<p local-id=3D"b17fadf53262">RAR and PAR together solve three critical prob=
lems in the authorization<br>
chain:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d52da2020947">
<li local-id=3D"576907765b17">
<p local-id=3D"cf542518ff4f"><strong>Semantic precision (RAR):</strong> The=
 AS receives the full transaction details<br>
via <code>authorization_details</code> =E2=80=94 amount, beneficiary IBAN, =
debtor account,<br>
remittance reference. It knows exactly what operation is being requested.</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"caa982776f1b">
<p local-id=3D"1f6158c9950a"><strong>User consent (RAR):</strong> Because t=
he AS has the transaction details, it<br>
renders an informed, transaction-specific consent screen. The user signs<br=
>
off on the exact operation, not a generic permission class. This satisfies<=
br>
PSD2 RTS Article 4 requirements for explicit, traceable consent.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2d2634ae74de">
<p local-id=3D"13e57250c462"><strong>Transport security (PAR):</strong> The=
 authorization request body never appears<br>
in a URL. Sensitive financial data is protected from proxy logs, browser<br=
>
history, SIEM infrastructure, and any intermediary system between the<br>
browser and the AS.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c8a645adebea">However, this combination does not solve a fou=
rth problem that is equally<br>
critical in a banking context: who is actually allowed to do what, under<br=
>
which conditions, at the moment of execution.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f10586ccf9b0">When the Resource Server receives a Bearer tok=
en containing<br><code>authorization_details</code>, it knows that the user=
 authenticated successfully<br>
and consented to a specific transfer. What the token alone cannot determine=
<br>
is whether that operation is currently permitted given the live state of th=
e<br>
system =E2=80=94 the user's role, their remaining daily limit, the current =
risk score<br>
of the transaction, or whether the destination account was flagged by the<b=
r>
fraud team an hour after consent was granted.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"a41aea5cb48c">
<h4 local-id=3D"667ca2d5c046" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-Level1=E2=80=94APIGa=
tewayenforcement(surfacecontrol)">Level 1 =E2=80=94 API Gateway enforcement=
 (surface control)</h4>
<p local-id=3D"18485e2623c5">The API Gateway acts as the first Policy Enfor=
cement Point (PEP). It<br>
intercepts every inbound request and performs the following controls:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f89769260a5e">
<li local-id=3D"30c0a0bd6e2b">
<p local-id=3D"cc588e1bb7e3">Validate the JWT signature against the AS publ=
ic key (JWKS endpoint)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"75ac3db8ea1e">
<p local-id=3D"7a3e79830337">Verify the token has not expired (<code>exp</c=
ode> claim)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a701b5d7f9f4">
<p local-id=3D"b389e545c8cf">Verify the token was issued by the expected AS=
 (<code>iss</code> claim)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"07c4543ecd9d">
<p local-id=3D"2e538ca7821c">Verify the audience matches the target service=
 (<code>aud</code> claim)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a2af9dd66fc">
<p local-id=3D"a99335174968">Verify the required scope is present (<code>wi=
re_transfer</code>)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"28c3e0007b39">
<p local-id=3D"74fe532280d4">Reject requests with missing or malformed Auth=
orization headers</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e10484abd868">
<p local-id=3D"3b2ad39679a5">Apply rate limiting per client and per token</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"297e38b87fe6">This level stops invalid, expired, and unsigne=
d tokens. It is necessary<br>
but it represents only surface-level enforcement:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"2f2a73899abe">
<li local-id=3D"64e934b50010">
<p local-id=3D"42836df83d1d">It does not evaluate whether the authenticated=
 user is allowed to perform<br>
this specific operation given their role and attributes.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4f5d3bd8dd86">
<p local-id=3D"4a069b3c70c3">It does not check business rules such as trans=
fer limits, approval<br>
thresholds, or beneficiary restrictions.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"99b6ca9df3ad">
<p local-id=3D"9d1911c44e19">It treats every valid token as equivalent, reg=
ardless of who holds it<br>
or what their current authorization context is.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bc0386474168">Level 1 enforcement filters out technically in=
valid requests. It enforces<br>
no business policy.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"31ede11a4097">
<h4 local-id=3D"e59788762b88" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-Level2=E2=80=94Resou=
rceServerenforcement(applicationcontrol)">Level 2 =E2=80=94 Resource Server=
 enforcement (application control)</h4>
<p local-id=3D"b9969224e4c7">The Resource Server implements a second enforc=
ement layer before executing<br>
any operation:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"51acaa50eee3">
<li local-id=3D"9d9f91aa11eb">
<p local-id=3D"c678ffdcbe15">Re-validate the JWT signature independently (n=
ever trust the gateway alone)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"198ef99e82b3">
<p local-id=3D"11eb6f83f324">Verify the <code>authorization_details</code> =
claim matches the request body exactly<br>
=E2=80=94 amount, currency, creditor IBAN, debtor IBAN, remittance referenc=
e</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8c9acc787404">
<p local-id=3D"73b801d8fd59">Verify the <code>sub</code> claim matches the =
authenticated user initiating the request</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4d40206d24d0">
<p local-id=3D"5f16436f01e3">Verify the token was not issued before the con=
sent session started<br>
(replay protection)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bdd0de351ce8">
<p local-id=3D"23515f73f638">Check that the debtor account in <code>authori=
zation_details</code> belongs to the<br>
authenticated user</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"71c8c5ee800f">
<p local-id=3D"31161fcef5dc">Reject any request where a single field in <co=
de>authorization_details</code> differs<br>
from the request body</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5bcd2a2bafa0">This level enforces token binding =E2=80=94 th=
e guarantee that the token presented<br>
corresponds exactly to the transaction the user consented to.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d7a133843f37">However, embedding all authorization logic at =
this level introduces<br>
structural problems that compound over time:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"cbf7165f27c3">
<li local-id=3D"e3faa8531ad0">
<p local-id=3D"b50b0eddc74f">Authorization rules are scattered across multi=
ple services and codebases,<br>
with no single view of the full policy set.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d3c068fa2a1d">
<p local-id=3D"7c564dc0f282">Business rules change faster than application =
release cycles allow,<br>
creating drift between the intended policy and what is actually enforced.</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"28f26d1bd39b">
<p local-id=3D"0c22da3dcf84">Vulnerabilities such as Broken Object Level Au=
thorization (BOLA),<br>
Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR), and privilege escalation bugs<br>
are difficult to detect when enforcement logic is embedded in application<b=
r>
code =E2=80=94 particularly when that logic was not formally documented at =
design<br>
time and has evolved incrementally across development iterations.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fb993442c6da">
<p local-id=3D"c0b4871b5d6b">Testing and auditing authorization coverage re=
quires deep knowledge of<br>
each service implementation, making compliance audits expensive and<br>
incomplete.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"26ff663553b4">Level 2 enforcement verifies token integrity a=
nd basic binding. It does not<br>
scale cleanly to complex, multi-attribute business policies.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"19215dd3aec8">
<h4 local-id=3D"36338ba7e2b8" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-Level3=E2=80=94Polic=
yDecisionPoint(dedicatedauthorizationengine)">Level 3 =E2=80=94 Policy Deci=
sion Point (dedicated authorization engine)</h4>
<p local-id=3D"f663e1878b14">The architectural response to the limitations =
of Levels 1 and 2 is to<br>
externalize authorization decisions into a dedicated Policy Decision Point.=
<br>
Instead of each service implementing its own authorization logic, every<br>
service calls a central PDP with the full request context and receives a<br=
>
structured permit or deny decision.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bb8cf69cad91">Policies are written, versioned, tested, and a=
udited in one place,<br>
independently of application code and deployment cycles. This is the model<=
br>
that banking architectures aligned with FAPI 2.0 and zero-trust principles<=
br>
are converging toward.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"a6dc90f76dc6">
<h3 local-id=3D"cbe4d506bd5f" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-3.2WhataPDPIsandWhat=
ItDoes">3.2 What a PDP Is and What It Does</h3>
<p local-id=3D"40c4be1163da">A Policy Decision Point is a dedicated compone=
nt in an access control<br>
architecture that evaluates authorization requests and returns an access<br=
>
decision based on predefined policies.</p>
<p local-id=3D"60f1ebbf2f8a">The PDP operates on three inputs:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7e39f4674f3d">
<li local-id=3D"9922a1c21e32">
<p local-id=3D"d23891ddfd2f"><strong>Subject:</strong> who is making the re=
quest =E2=80=94 the authenticated user, their<br>
roles, their attributes, their organizational context</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d622360f2fc6">
<p local-id=3D"5a4b4c26014e"><strong>Resource:</strong> what is being acces=
sed or modified =E2=80=94 the transfer endpoint,<br>
the target account, the requested amount</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5047cc4f53ee">
<p local-id=3D"53a982ffd099"><strong>Context:</strong> the current state of=
 the environment =E2=80=94 time of day, remaining<br>
daily limit, real-time risk score, account status, fraud watchlist state</p=
></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"22c1f5596354">The PDP evaluates these inputs against a polic=
y set and returns a structured<br>
decision =E2=80=94 permit or deny =E2=80=94 along with any obligations or a=
dvice the PEP<br>
must apply before executing the operation.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fb659b30e9d9">Key architectural properties of the PDP:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"43d8c60f58fb">
<li local-id=3D"358ea33c38e3">
<p local-id=3D"debc717381d2">It is stateless from the perspective of the ca=
lling service =E2=80=94 the caller<br>
provides all the context, the PDP evaluates and responds.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c8b79852d5e6">
<p local-id=3D"7a893d28b90d">It has no side effects =E2=80=94 it does not e=
xecute the operation, it does not<br>
modify data, it only decides.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"68925e5d9208">
<p local-id=3D"69cfcea4ba8e">It is decoupled from the application =E2=80=94=
 policy updates do not require<br>
application redeployment.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cf24d2baaddf">
<p local-id=3D"c3533c565fdf">It provides a single, auditable point for all =
authorization decisions<br>
across the system.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"465ea35c8be9">The component that calls the PDP is called the=
 <strong>Policy Enforcement Point</strong><br><strong>(PEP)</strong>. In a =
banking architecture, the Resource Server acts as the PEP for<br>
business operations. The API Gateway acts as a PEP for transport-level<br>
controls. The AS acts as a PEP at consent time.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"259b5fdc9cbe">
<h3 local-id=3D"d77b34dd9128" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-3.3PDPintheBankingWi=
reTransferFlow">3.3 PDP in the Banking Wire Transfer Flow</h3>
<p local-id=3D"b7034289ec34">In a banking wire transfer architecture combin=
ing RAR, PAR, and a PDP, the Resource Server does not execute the transfer =
as soon as it receives a valid token. Before executing, it calls the PDP wi=
th the full context of the request and waits for a permit decision.</p>
<p local-id=3D"362dfc118230"></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">sequenc=
eDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C   as Client (SPA)
    participant AS  as Authorization Server
    participant U   as User (Browser)
    participant GW  as API Gateway (PEP Level 1)
    participant RS  as Resource Server (PEP Level 2)
    participant PDP as Policy Decision Point (Level 3)
    C-&gt;&gt;AS: POST /par via fetch() =E2=80=94 body: authorization_detai=
ls [{amount:47500, iban:FR76...}]
    Note over AS: Stores request server-side =E2=80=94 returns opaque refer=
ence
    AS-&gt;&gt;C: { request_uri: urn:ietf:...xyz, expires_in: 60 }
    C-&gt;&gt;U: redirect to browser
    U-&gt;&gt;AS: GET /authorize?client_id=3Dwire-transfer-spa&amp;request_=
uri=3Durn:ietf:...xyz
    Note over U,AS: No sensitive data in URL
    opt No valid SSO session
        AS-&gt;&gt;U: Login page
        U-&gt;&gt;AS: Credentials
    end
    AS-&gt;&gt;U: Consent page =E2=80=94 amount: 47500 EUR, IBAN: FR76..., =
beneficiary: ACME Corp
    U-&gt;&gt;AS: Confirm transaction
    AS-&gt;&gt;C: 302 =E2=80=94 callback?code=3DAUTH_CODE
    C-&gt;&gt;AS: POST /token (code + code_verifier)
    AS-&gt;&gt;C: access_token { sub, roles, authorization_details: [{...}]=
 }

    C-&gt;&gt;GW: POST /transfers (Bearer token + body: {amount:47500, iban=
:FR76...})

    note over GW: Level 1 controls
    GW-&gt;&gt;GW: Validate JWT signature (JWKS)
    GW-&gt;&gt;GW: Check exp, iss, aud claims
    GW-&gt;&gt;GW: Check scope wire_transfer present
    GW-&gt;&gt;GW: Apply rate limiting

    alt Invalid token or missing scope
        GW-&gt;&gt;C: 401 Unauthorized
    else Valid =E2=80=94 forward to RS
        GW-&gt;&gt;RS: forward request + token

        note over RS: Level 2 controls
        RS-&gt;&gt;RS: Re-validate JWT signature independently
        RS-&gt;&gt;RS: Compare token.authorization_details vs request body
        RS-&gt;&gt;RS: Verify sub matches authenticated user
        RS-&gt;&gt;RS: Verify debtor account belongs to sub

        alt authorization_details mismatch
            RS-&gt;&gt;C: 403 Forbidden =E2=80=94 token binding failed
        else Token binding verified =E2=80=94 call PDP

            RS-&gt;&gt;PDP: POST /authorize { subject: {id, roles, daily_sp=
ent}, action: wire_transfer, resource: {amount:47500, creditor_iban:FR76...=
, debtor_iban:FR76...}, context: {time, risk_score} }

            note over PDP: Level 3 policy evaluation
            PDP-&gt;&gt;PDP: Evaluate role policy =E2=80=94 is PAYER role p=
resent?
            PDP-&gt;&gt;PDP: Evaluate amount vs daily limit
            PDP-&gt;&gt;PDP: Evaluate creditor IBAN against fraud watchlist
            PDP-&gt;&gt;PDP: Evaluate dual-control rule if amount above thr=
eshold

            alt Permit
                PDP-&gt;&gt;RS: { decision: PERMIT }
                RS-&gt;&gt;RS: Execute transfer
                RS-&gt;&gt;C: 200 OK
            else Deny
                PDP-&gt;&gt;RS: { decision: DENY, reason: "daily_limit_exce=
eded" }
                RS-&gt;&gt;C: 403 Forbidden =E2=80=94 policy denied
            end
        end
    end
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"3f183398a9fe"></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"abb129b9a7f3" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-3.4WhatthePDPEvaluat=
es=E2=80=94PolicyCategories">3.4 What the PDP Evaluates =E2=80=94 Policy Ca=
tegories</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8bfff35cf898"><strong>Identity and role policies =E2=80=94 W=
ho</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"fa82ede2-31bc-481d-8389-58b47013fcd8">
<li local-id=3D"40b8ddf2-9bbc-4358-94e3-2f171327e1a4">
<p local-id=3D"ebe2d60e7772">The PDP checks if the user has the right role =
to perform the requested action.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f544f2cd-31ed-4050-849a-53bdf8723b9b">
<p local-id=3D"01649e56a003">Having one role does not give access to everyt=
hing =E2=80=94 each role grants only what it is explicitly allowed to do.</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a3c5118c-0669-4337-b0fe-a170a4589ca6">
<p local-id=3D"a6623ac10d77">Access can be limited to specific groups.</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8d79fa700ef2"><strong>Attribute-based policies =E2=80=94 Wha=
t</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ca8e173a614b">
<li local-id=3D"2cc13b857188">
<p local-id=3D"cbe286b4fa98">Decisions are made against <strong>subject att=
ributes</strong> =E2=80=94 limits, quotas, flags,<br>
and classifications assigned to the user or the resource.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"62e25e15e04f">
<p local-id=3D"55391e0c5364">A request that is valid from a role perspectiv=
e can still be denied if<br>
a subject-level attribute prohibits it.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"786199f818f3">
<p local-id=3D"325944e01939"><strong>Resource attributes</strong> =E2=80=94=
 sensitivity level, ownership, classification =E2=80=94 are<br>
evaluated independently from subject attributes.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"afb4f4e44f5a"><strong>Resource attributes</strong> are prope=
rties of the payment or approval object being accessed. The PDP evaluates t=
hem <strong>independently </strong>from <strong>who is making the request</=
strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"32ee4b632e39"><strong>Examples </strong>in a payment and app=
roval context:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"4861e923-85b9-421e-a4bf-97fc756bac9a">
<li local-id=3D"34c38c26-ad30-40c9-ab0a-8b0f28f14232">
<p local-id=3D"770c91968c82"><strong>Amount threshold</strong> =E2=80=94 a =
payment above 50,000 EUR is classified as "high-value" and requires a secon=
d approver, regardless of the initiator's role</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6b06505e-bcfe-42c2-bed6-ae585fdbde0a">
<p local-id=3D"82eca1467cd1"><strong>Approval status</strong> =E2=80=94 a p=
ayment already in "pending approval" state cannot be modified or re-submitt=
ed until the current approval cycle is completed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"593dab23-58ed-4f76-aa0f-b68b6085e0c6">
<p local-id=3D"4d83961e379d"><strong>Initiator lock</strong> =E2=80=94 a pa=
yment created by user A cannot be approved by user A, even if user A holds =
the MANAGER role =E2=80=94 the payment itself carries the initiator's ident=
ity as an attribute</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d0c10a03-d3bc-4306-a861-2ddde7d01568">
<p local-id=3D"860908709635"><strong>Payment type</strong> =E2=80=94 an int=
ernational wire transfer is classified differently from a domestic transfer=
 and triggers additional policy checks at the PDP level</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a2319f7e-d98a-4e78-a1ac-ecd73e1e9e5b">
<p local-id=3D"15c506f9d66e"><strong>Expiry</strong> =E2=80=94 an approval =
request that has been pending for more than 24 hours is automatically class=
ified as "expired" and denied by the PDP without any user action</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1d7bc5086863">Technically, the PDP sees the data like this. =
:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "subject":  { "id": "user_1", "roles": ["MANAGER"] },
  "action":   "approve",
  "resource": { "id": "PAY-2024-089", "status": "pending_approval",
                "initiator_id": "user_2", "amount": 47500, "risk_level": "h=
igh" }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"031e06d0e27c"><strong>Contextual and environmental policies =
=E2=80=94 When / Where</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"1528fda08fa8">
<li local-id=3D"e8db0240-1be9-4872-804b-357594bb62de">
<p local-id=3D"55069fcf96bb">The PDP evaluates conditions that exist at the=
 moment of execution, not at the moment the token was issued.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8d2418e3-66c5-4622-bce9-d2321ce0f05c">
<p local-id=3D"9aa38bc061a9"><strong>Examples of contextual inputs</strong>=
: time of day, user location, device trust level, real-time risk score of t=
he transaction.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fbaa8584-4a11-4c31-be92-35b7fb3d0152">
<p local-id=3D"a8c671533797">A <strong><span data-colorid=3D"r07d7i7k7n">to=
ken can be valid</span></strong> and a user can have <strong><span data-col=
orid=3D"yaquh04w9n">the right role</span></strong> =E2=80=94 and the operat=
ion can still <strong><span data-colorid=3D"vt0d1lmuw7">be denied</span> </=
strong>because something changed between <strong>consent and execution</str=
ong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"695f2414ae0d"></p>
<p local-id=3D"2853b6b80660">ABAC with a PDP is the pragmatic choice for ba=
nking authorization: <strong>policies are evaluated against attributes alre=
ady available in the token</strong> or retrievable in real time, <strong>wi=
th no need to model </strong>and maintain a persistent relationship graph.<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"92874b0ded67">ReBAC (FGA) adds expressive power for ownershi=
p and hierarchical structures<strong> but requires a significant upfront</s=
trong> investment in <strong>relationship modeling and ongoing tuple</stron=
g> maintenance</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"993e95b4-5403-4497-bb49-e7d=
094275b8d" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5ed0f7d2-5526-4643-bede-3cfcb0edd109">
<th data-local-id=3D"e128c119-efd4-4391-9d1f-8ced711864c0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"b09f0d113ef8">Criterion</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"44c52a2e-f457-4704-ae5c-12478880407f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"78a261b5f180">Classic OAuth 2.0</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"0b56bee0-c04d-4d72-a238-99d6e44ff198" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2ee68af08750">OAuth 2.0 + PAR + RAR + PDP (ABAC)</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"f1b70667-f7f5-45df-b511-c5746d011e17" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"820a49b938e8">OAuth 2.0 + PAR + RAR + FGA (ReBAC)</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"180e7847-7c58-40c4-aa12-f1819c637c30">
<td data-local-id=3D"0242c156-f2c7-41d6-b4c9-54d9aec00a93" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f5343ef4ae12">Authorization type</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8d652677-118f-459c-9bc0-05feaafa0746" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5118e6491669">RBAC</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4ff6d88c-b9a7-40b7-9b64-33bb888bafeb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"81315ae2b849">ABAC</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5473538c-9266-43ae-9717-2f02c8ec9714" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"418134682003">ReBAC</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"dac156f7-099c-47c0-983a-0ca8d26ed67e">
<td data-local-id=3D"84f9a6e8-3a27-4ea0-bdea-74f44c5de945" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ee39c7a55ae0">Authorization granularity</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"30a3da68-ab65-4772-a541-35b4613d6b68" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a584c393b35b">Coarse =E2=80=94 role or scope only</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"09d97f95-248d-4481-8337-15afd0779a9c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"073e67e19be2">Fine =E2=80=94 roles + attributes + context</p=
></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c7cfad0f-e693-4ed8-bf0b-34c6568a6660" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b3f8d71cf5b4">Very fine =E2=80=94 relationship graph between=
 subjects and resources</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"efe34103-f110-4af9-aecb-22707a4504a0">
<td data-local-id=3D"cb13ad61-6779-4038-877a-057172d95f6b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edc00a7294f5">Policy model</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a497c99a-d15f-42c8-b45b-78e0acd225d9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cde2e91e5233">Static roles mapped to scopes</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"539e11b9-15fd-4a75-9b67-b1123ed8abd3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"625cab3bdb4a">Rules evaluated against attributes at runtime<=
/p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fbe467fc-8a76-43b9-bc9e-fac5fcc94766" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2f5364dedfe9">Relationship tuples evaluated against a typed =
model</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ffbb4a91-3810-4617-a16d-bc01a3191382">
<td data-local-id=3D"a03f809e-e07f-4a6a-9cfd-54238116be28" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"78a86a17b953">Data model complexity</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0db89e28-5a1c-4bb8-b1b0-c0be548d195a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"30509c6c0062">Low =E2=80=94 roles assigned to users</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"58eb1902-e827-4a16-97f3-e363ad4748d9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eabbf048774e">Medium =E2=80=94 attributes on users and resou=
rces</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8fd7cddb-8eb4-4084-bd6e-58a067a2ccef" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"067b4cbbf21c">High =E2=80=94 full relationship graph must be=
 modeled and persisted</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6e7301ff-ada3-42af-9e7e-7d873cd7a46d">
<td data-local-id=3D"2bdd679f-a7ac-432a-aed4-b29e188adfff" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9e2db5eed21f">Implementation effort</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f6b0723a-2537-45c8-b83c-7151d11240ed" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b499921b4d19">Low</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"bbbcda88-d197-4ea2-a70b-6f1f96ec3a41" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b0ebc5b6bea9">Medium</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d72262a2-7f52-4e25-912d-8c76d8753bf5" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3198b8a15fcc">High</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a8817d22-4eba-43aa-b4ab-3f83cbe75eb5">
<td data-local-id=3D"c8ed8865-acae-4e9b-8ed9-b7362bbdb92b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f08577f80ca5">Policy update</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e6f9e429-8454-4f5f-964e-d58a321c35b7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c87d9b7d2f8e">Requires code or config change</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"90723458-d6fc-4366-9c0e-bcf2be48d814" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3e399b4d2a30">Policy update in PDP engine only</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1d6d762e-f381-4763-8d55-90fccef914a9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a0b487e8c5a5">Model + tuple update in FGA store</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0d6e9952-2d6c-441c-ae99-8ace3708d7f3">
<td data-local-id=3D"d6a0e744-c9ab-41a8-add4-1e7723ec5b04" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"486332df4b87">Real-time context support</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"42f2acd3-ec7a-4607-9bd8-88bbd3e12bf0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"93d5379002e0">No</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f5c8d97a-0c88-4fde-bac5-df34c1962f05" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2311c905434d">Yes =E2=80=94 risk score, time, location evalu=
ated at decision time</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6556dbdb-fcaf-41d9-ac3f-68705d15d736" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1590d068a3bb">Partial =E2=80=94 depends on relationship fres=
hness</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b2ad0d2f-1fd2-454c-86a1-893a2d73b6e3">
<td data-local-id=3D"f4461dd1-1d49-4fbe-ae9d-5b59f5d8b882" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fb82cd4d53d3">Transaction-level binding (RAR)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2f705f03-4bd7-4519-8404-70cb53985240" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b67ceeed0f22">No</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dd9d8214-3b89-4e22-bc3c-aa1274bfd2aa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"36e4576272b8">Yes</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"cdf3afff-a7d4-42b9-95e6-e0575dbcca50" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cfc2daf1f4fa">Yes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2f29ce29-4b92-4da7-8c98-c6ab525281f3">
<td data-local-id=3D"6af4bde2-56d5-4f6a-a8e3-11d05b84011c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6cd296f86a23">Transport security (PAR)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4c5cb1f5-3b50-466f-9b30-a9c90db86121" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f74924bcee29">No</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a0ab69e4-a9c4-4ab4-9741-15ad3f4aa092" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a48d051f6a83">Yes</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7d42cca2-e10d-4ce0-8038-73a7c0ad6ba4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"640fae8975c1">Yes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4ba2d7f7-0df9-4513-9700-ba566e6540d5">
<td data-local-id=3D"4e7c1c38-c7e0-456e-b93c-0022cc06a7f1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"16addbcf9e71">Consent precision</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"70cbe5da-dae7-4622-9755-8f684e4fe61b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ff995b3fde07">Generic scope</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"98e6a7aa-1f50-479f-abbb-2172986409df" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a12f85a62401">Transaction-specific via authorization_details=
</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a4db7590-ecbe-4a41-b523-02263cf9df1f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"84408e067a47">Transaction-specific via authorization_details=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d1f90c09-c0dd-4beb-b7a1-f53b627faa3e">
<td data-local-id=3D"b8e15117-dd40-48ef-8e82-ebc2a9cd0b98" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a307514abf17">Scales to complex org hierarchies</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"37950a0f-8669-4728-a555-f67c517ff50c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8213755e4ddd">No</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"010a3fe8-d4bb-4ca9-a9d1-da2b858b5d4b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"db00a7116a6a">Partially =E2=80=94 attribute rules can approx=
imate hierarchies</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4fdcc3c4-aae4-43bb-af9d-e6850390ebc9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c8444a68e8c0">Yes =E2=80=94 hierarchy is native to the model=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b53e784a-1472-481d-9c4c-65d1741e2779">
<td data-local-id=3D"1fcd6c26-99e2-45d3-a099-19c50df9c07c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7104594d9f52">Scales to fine-grained resource ownership</p><=
/td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8e1cab23-3daa-41fe-a2c5-c88f87e90883" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4c634999e078">No</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"80fd6b00-ca1f-42c8-945d-fe3f545aa285" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f00403453f5f">Partially</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d43424b5-27fa-45f6-af0d-fd12a3ed062f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ee61725e8b27">Yes =E2=80=94 ownership is a first-class relat=
ionship</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1909e45c-a845-4e13-b855-72db992699c4">
<td data-local-id=3D"323506aa-38ec-4241-ae7c-7a777a4af59a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c5b32c30e318">Typical use case</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"50edca53-aea1-45d1-99a0-0c040eabca6c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ee4b153fcf5c">Simple API access control</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1f6af00f-323b-4496-847d-da869ec96b8b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f923bcf4eb6d">Banking, payment APIs, regulated environments<=
/p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4e370c00-21cc-4386-9dc1-faf091c5247e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5ecd50d2bbd9">Multi-tenant SaaS, document sharing, complex o=
rg structures</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"13646112-cb46-48d7-8770-d6bffe8d4545">
<td data-local-id=3D"0e41237a-eba7-4aaf-b0eb-aaa41af7528b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7c1a91d34f09">Example engines</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"083ff319-4b77-4d5b-afb0-764845ed537e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ded341fc6fd0">Keycloak roles, OAuth scopes</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5e6ad5de-cd69-4835-88e3-b18fd74a1b54" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"741eb17f8298">OPA, PingOne Authorize, AWS Cedar</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f705c591-44c8-4a13-8b17-a88eb355b63b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"81c359751b6a">OpenFGA, SpiceDB, Permify</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b4a3a081-56a1-4fd7-9d2a-28898dfefba5">
<td data-local-id=3D"da66ba54-ba70-4a5b-9a3d-ca0c5c2765dc" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e7d0f5ea62f9">PSD2 RTS compliance</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c1b5493d-aac0-4954-af47-ada95b3ecbe4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f620b792294d">Insufficient</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"51e20e63-e544-4f1f-aba8-39600033d238" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"18e76681853e">Full when combined with RAR</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1aeafff9-07e5-4fc9-b62d-d8be477344cf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7311ae6b5df8">Full when combined with RAR</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"22f9eda5830c" id=3D"OAuth2.0SecurityPatterns=E2=80=94FromCo=
arse-GrainedAuthorizationtotoFine-GrainedAuthorization-Glossary{#glossary}"=
>Glossary {#glossary}</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5d=
fa63b8-6159-4156-880b-caf0620376f4" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e4f897bd-3c62-47e1-8aec-7e5504f13e6d">
<th data-local-id=3D"c21755e0-f4cf-4830-98f1-3a8659a58c7d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"d25cdf2a15bc">Term</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"99944ead-d344-452f-87a4-88feba0904a0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9bf4e49bc6d7">Definition</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"8da6a59a-60e1-4ab2-aac2-103a2e158a36">
<td data-local-id=3D"a2d0e462-bc3a-4fe2-a7e3-34effd6ddf4d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fe2b41cac478"><strong>AS (Authorization Server)</strong></p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"088c4180-914a-4504-b789-6068731a4e6e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2aacafa9a924">The server that authenticates the resource own=
er and issues access tokens after obtaining authorization. In banking conte=
xts, examples include Keycloak, PingFederate, ForgeRock AM, and PingOne.</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cca5a81d-430e-4c96-bbdd-2842007b7d07">
<td data-local-id=3D"9ca736e5-ea8f-44a3-9258-99a7353c1f2f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b9390c245edd"><strong>authorization_details</strong></p></td=
>
<td data-local-id=3D"8183ff6c-015a-47fb-8dda-44f11101a387" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"aa2dd6085660">The JSON parameter introduced by RFC 9396 (RAR=
) that carries a structured, type-tagged description of the specific author=
ization being requested. Replaces or supplements the coarse <code>scope</co=
de> string for fine-grained use cases.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6f57ab6e-b43e-46ec-b2dc-3cea76b86841">
<td data-local-id=3D"add99546-77e1-4592-bcb7-436b74abf34f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"df980b64fed1"><strong>Authorization Code Flow</strong></p></=
td>
<td data-local-id=3D"74ef8231-6398-4b02-b892-8d6c951804d2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"84b154b61a13">The OAuth 2.0 grant type in which the AS issue=
s a short-lived authorization code to the client via a browser redirect, wh=
ich the client then exchanges for an access token via a back-channel POST t=
o the token endpoint.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"6ca4d595-24ee-4e20-a572-332ca99a16e4">
<td data-local-id=3D"723e3b2c-d6ed-4b56-b7db-f31b96e8b471" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b1e5a8b2ea64"><strong>Bearer Token</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"341e4d1d-2459-4af7-8364-7e15f6d32456" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7507c879a134">An access token that grants access to a protec=
ted resource to any party that presents it, without requiring proof of iden=
tity. Defined in RFC 6750.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"785e931a-30cf-403d-a3a9-2b2b5196a24d">
<td data-local-id=3D"0352bff2-bbaf-439d-afc9-67c84365829b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"25e49878ed04"><strong>Client</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"db81ada0-625e-4570-8310-dbc0c14a83b6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0aa1bdc8cbe6">In OAuth 2.0 terminology, the application requ=
esting authorization on behalf of the resource owner. In the banking POC co=
ntext, this is the SPA or mobile application.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"dbaaae0d-fdc6-48ce-bad1-c57874bb9c52">
<td data-local-id=3D"22d5b995-d2f6-4d74-a558-8d0e04ae2f80" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e7344f52b836"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://ope=
nid.net/specs/fapi-security-profile-2_0.html" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>FAPI=
 (Financial-grade API)</strong></a></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"43bd20c7-f3cd-4a11-ba8c-1379bf6abb5d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fcd6c3d62ded">A set of security profiles published by the Op=
enID Foundation, built on top of OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect, that mandate=
s PAR and RAR for payment initiation and account access APIs in financial s=
ervices.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2a36aece-9ab4-48dd-83d9-0653373a841e">
<td data-local-id=3D"886c863f-7688-4753-8e99-9a1297906a25" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c490da898eb5"><strong>PAR (Pushed Authorization Requests)</s=
trong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9ad5fe27-074b-4ea3-9014-a281553c6dbe" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9b8b1c2b0016">RFC 9126. An OAuth 2.0 extension that allows c=
lients to send the Authorization Request to the AS via an authenticated bac=
k-channel HTTPS POST to a <code>/par</code> endpoint, receiving an opaque <=
code>request_uri</code> in return. This <code>request_uri</code> is then us=
ed in the browser redirect, keeping all request parameters out of URLs.</p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"620b4b76-4ad3-420d-ba0b-19befaea3f0e">
<td data-local-id=3D"6019d423-37ac-418a-8bf1-b03d14b2c667" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5792ed1f83a9"><strong>PKCE (Proof Key for Code Exchange)</st=
rong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"41cf9ac0-b476-45e5-9cf5-293c194aaac7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"70d4bbd040cc">RFC 7636. A security extension to the Authoriz=
ation Code flow that prevents authorization code interception attacks. The =
client generates a random <code>code_verifier</code>, derives a <code>code_=
challenge</code> from it, sends the challenge in the Authorization Request,=
 and proves possession of the verifier at the token endpoint. Mandatory for=
 public clients.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c91804e5-16ff-46f2-a647-f11a168165d6">
<td data-local-id=3D"071462b8-8828-454c-b0b9-d9ad1f4b4b2e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9b07f147135c"><strong>PSD2 (Payment Services Directive 2)</s=
trong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"def758a2-2acf-4ea8-afb6-6de61b153696" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"799106b89ca6">European Union directive (2015/2366) that regu=
lates payment services and payment service providers. Requires Strong Custo=
mer Authentication (SCA) and explicit, transaction-specific user consent fo=
r payment initiation.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ed2326f9-a7c0-48c1-860b-9029057a14fb">
<td data-local-id=3D"0c9257e7-87b8-4569-8678-a6e825d7c38c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e26c1cdf0f5e"><strong>Public Client</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7b4c3728-5433-4a7a-a3e3-19fd59ba463c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"64beea02e430">An OAuth 2.0 client that cannot securely store=
 a client secret =E2=80=94 typically a browser-based SPA or a mobile applic=
ation. Public clients rely on PKCE rather than client credentials for secur=
ity.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"236f0615-c950-4afa-9ffa-e28ad8909636">
<td data-local-id=3D"ff4a4ec5-a7fc-4c65-a8fd-6aa15ca6ffc8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e7f409c39fd6"><strong>RAR (Rich Authorization Requests)</str=
ong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4e396d7f-e17c-404a-ba89-6a725a3dcccc" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c520b7d1a4d0">RFC 9396. An OAuth 2.0 extension that introduc=
es the <code>authorization_details</code> parameter, enabling clients to sp=
ecify fine-grained, structured authorization requests beyond what the <code=
>scope</code> parameter can express.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"aaef1c33-91cb-4b4a-8215-19738889c228">
<td data-local-id=3D"5f5fc735-6aac-4f96-b4fe-6ef60affb386" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7cc8c4465de9"><strong>Redirect URI</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fde10ce0-94c5-4a95-892c-35947a32d5a3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2794ca51212a">The URI to which the AS redirects the user age=
nt after the authorization step, carrying the authorization code (or error)=
. Must be pre-registered with the AS.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9fd2669a-3489-4397-9a77-48daa0e56b18">
<td data-local-id=3D"62c8fbd2-4d97-44f5-af2c-4fa06f6f4f24" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"83d296293de5"><strong>request_uri</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"73560a0d-211c-4692-a963-c38b83ed877a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"45397455d51f">The opaque, short-lived URI returned by the AS=
 in response to a PAR request. It serves as a reference to the stored Autho=
rization Request and is the only parameter (besides <code>client_id</code>)=
 required in the subsequent browser redirect.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5c0b2224-4de0-43e9-9a5d-1ae1f388d72b">
<td data-local-id=3D"c35c5f21-ced9-4a54-85b1-7e989ecf8fea" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3750e55dc667"><strong>Resource Owner</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d71c377b-6f1b-4595-b6fc-1d4ce0722a96" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d49fe39e498b">The entity (typically the end user) that owns =
the protected resource and can grant access to it.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"add16438-e59f-4038-bfcd-0c098717bf81">
<td data-local-id=3D"471a82c4-762e-4898-8880-7120997d79e1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fb696b5792c6"><strong>Resource Server (RS)</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"979a8887-ed6c-435a-9e75-276c52e93995" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"15adc197ffcb">The server hosting the protected resources =E2=
=80=94 in a banking context, the backend API that processes wire transfer r=
equests, account queries, etc.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4007750a-6d66-4f3f-ae4a-5f7207674804">
<td data-local-id=3D"f154fb44-2713-4774-a713-73eb88831957" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"105201c48697"><strong>RTS (Regulatory Technical Standards)</=
strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3ec24f1d-0c7c-4161-bbe6-12856afbf583" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d6dfa77faa77">Commission Delegated Regulation (EU) 2018/389,=
 which specifies the technical requirements for Strong Customer Authenticat=
ion and secure communication under PSD2.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"87a7feac-32d4-4581-9ed1-7662e41de6bf">
<td data-local-id=3D"23d9755d-ea4c-406d-b2fe-87ef65e1bb4d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b61960e5af6d"><strong>SCA (Strong Customer Authentication)</=
strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c90b73d0-d698-4fd4-a0df-5af5f6f23cc2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"65a29263f25b">An authentication procedure defined by PSD2 RT=
S that requires the use of two or more independent authentication factors (=
knowledge, possession, inherence) for payment initiation and account access=
.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9f0a9350-e9ac-4f04-b2a4-55c81feb3ce8">
<td data-local-id=3D"7743eb81-83b7-4c0a-9a59-f59538a5c1c4" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"377688f4f48b"><strong>scope</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dd300038-410c-425e-8963-a52e7d1f16e9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"535c15e611a0">The OAuth 2.0 mechanism for specifying the acc=
ess permissions being requested. A space-separated string of identifiers (e=
.g., <code>openid wire_transfer accounts:read</code>). Coarse-grained by de=
sign; does not carry transaction-specific data.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"337e4022-74bf-4f9e-830a-848ca5fd3eaa">
<td data-local-id=3D"e03747f7-d364-4ee5-8434-57736a9f67fa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5eea64e76dab"><strong>SPA (Single Page Application)</strong>=
</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8ae98a5a-ee1e-4df8-813b-0f546cf847d7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9986d34c27c7">A web application that loads a single HTML pag=
e and dynamically updates content via JavaScript. SPAs are public OAuth 2.0=
 clients and must use PKCE.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"66cde706-3211-46a6-8ac5-d160a0c341d6">
<td data-local-id=3D"eae6a9ff-605c-4b45-9a53-194f60790dc1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"94e9eb31bb17"><strong>TLS (Transport Layer Security)</strong=
></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1a079a75-3d65-49b4-bb72-3551394dad52" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d104f8255ffe">The cryptographic protocol that provides confi=
dentiality and integrity for network communications. HTTPS is HTTP over TLS=
. TLS protects the content of HTTP request bodies but does not protect URLs=
, which may be logged by intermediaries.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2afc1462-8b2e-4170-b72b-ddb8e773b2eb">
<td data-local-id=3D"e8e1ab6b-779f-4cff-91eb-39907f2ba817" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d0748181418c"><strong>Token Binding</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7131d374-fcee-4b18-8a18-27d858dc553f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d5099f527fbd">The property by which an access token is crypt=
ographically or semantically tied to a specific transaction intent. With RA=
R, token binding is achieved by embedding <code>authorization_details</code=
> as a claim in the issued token.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
